  "Question": "<p>Wrt Ramsey numbers I have the following identity given to me:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_135\"><math alttext=\"R(m,n)\\leq R(m-1,n)+R(m,n-1)\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>\u2264</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>,</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>,</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>And i have the following bases cases: <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_136\"><math alttext=\"R(m,2)=m\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_137\"><math alttext=\"R(2,n)=n\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span>. One has to prove that:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_138\"><math alttext=\"R(m,n)\\leq\\left(\\begin{array}[]{c}{m+n-2}\\\\ {m-1}\\end{array}\\right)\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>\u2264</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtable rowspacing=\"0pt\"><mtr><mtd columnalign=\"center\"><mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd columnalign=\"center\"><mrow><mi>m</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>It is obvious that we have to go on splitting the two terms on the RHS into pairs of terms decrementing the indices by 1 each time. But the appearance of the combination is non-obvious.</p>",
